; Coverage for op.cc lines 520-522:
; When a function call throws a non-recursion exception, the catch
; handler at line 520 adds context about which function was called
; and rethrows. Here justify() receives amount/0 which throws
; "Divide by zero" inside the function call.

2024/01/01 Test
    Expenses:Food    $100.00
    Assets:Cash

test reg --format "%(justify(amount / 0, 20))\n" -> 1
__ERROR__
While evaluating value expression:
  justify((amount / 0), 20)
While calling function 'justify (<#EXPR (amount / {0})>, <#EXPR {20}>)':
While handling posting from "$FILE", line 8:
>     Expenses:Food    $100.00
Error: Divide by zero
end test
